mate, head up.

507
00:28:50,740 --> 00:28:51,866
Steady yourself!

508
00:28:52,740 --> 00:28:53,787
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

509
00:28:53,860 --> 00:28:56,670
Little help?
Help! Help!

510
00:28:56,740 --> 00:28:59,027
Mike, you good?

511
00:28:59,100 --> 00:29:00,181
Are these ladders
gonna take two?

512
00:29:00,260 --> 00:29:01,750
Yeah, I'll get a rope,
I'll belay you.

513
00:29:01,820 --> 00:29:02,981
Just stay right
where you are, mate.

514
00:29:03,060 --> 00:29:04,141
I can't pull myself up!

515
00:29:04,220 --> 00:29:06,621
I'm gonna come out to you.

516
00:29:06,700 --> 00:29:07,747
Okay.

517
00:29:07,820 --> 00:29:08,821
You're good,
Beck, you're okay.

518
00:29:08,900 --> 00:29:09,947
Got it for you.

519
00:29:10,020 --> 00:29:11,146
Right, tie me
in, Scott, tie me in.

520
00:29:11,220 --> 00:29:12,267
Come and get me!

521
00:29:12,340 --> 00:29:13,751
- On belay?
- Got it. On belay.

522
00:29:13,820 --> 00:29:15,106
Let's go.

523
00:29:15,180 --> 00:29:17,581
Right, I'm coming out to you, Beck.
Here I come, mate.

524
00:29:23,420 --> 00:29:25,991
Nice and easy,
you're tied in, mate.

525
00:29:27,020 --> 00:29:28,260
I can't
feel my hands.

526
00:29:28,340 --> 00:29:29,546
You're looking good.

527
00:29:29,620 --> 00:29:31,110
Grab me.
Beck, Beck, Beck.

528
00:29:31,220 --> 00:29:33,188
Grab me!
Stay right where you are, mate.

529
00:29:33,260 --> 00:29:34,500
I'm right here,
I'm coming to you.

530
00:29:34,580 --> 00:29:36,503
I can't pull myself up!

531
00:29:36,580 --> 00:29:37,820
I got ya.

532
00:29:46,620 --> 00:29:47,951
You okay?

533
00:29:49,180 --> 00:29:51,990
There's no guarantee
to the summit, I get it.

534
00:29:52,060 --> 00:29:54,062
But to get killed
because I'm waiting in line

535
00:29:54,140 --> 00:29:56,461
like I'm in
freaking Walmart.

536
00:29:56,580 --> 00:29:59,902
That's not why I
paid you 65,000 dollars.

537
00:29:59,980 --> 00:30:01,584
Now get me off of here.

538
00:30:03,140 --> 00:30:06,144
That's it.
Plant your feet one at a time.

539
00:30:12,700 --> 00:30:14,140
All right,
thanks for coming by.

540
00:30:14,180 --> 00:30:15,180
Uh...

541
00:30:15,220 --> 00:30:18,622
Look, Base Camp's,
you know, chockablock full this year, so,

542
00:30:18,700 --> 00:30:20,748
I think it would
all benefit us greatly

543
00:30:20,820 --> 00:30:22,026
by coming together
like this

544
00:30:22,100 --> 00:30:24,387
and, you know, working out
some kind of plan and schedule.

545
00:30:24,460 --> 00:30:25,791
What, like some
kind of rota?

546
00:30:25,900 --> 00:30:26,947
Yes.

547
00:30:27,020 --> 00:30:28,351
On Everest?

548
00:30:30,140 --> 00:30:31,740
Everyone knows
Everest is a business

549
00:30:31,780 --> 00:30:33,464
for you, Robert,
are you kidding?

550
00:30:33,540 --> 00:30:34,666
What gives you
the right to tell us

551
00:30:34,740 --> 00:30:35,741
when we can climb
and when we can't?

552
00:30:35,820 --> 00:30:37,709
I'm not telling you, mate.
I'm asking.

553
00:30:38,300 --> 00:30:40,700
If we know when everybody's
planning to summit, for instance,

554
00:30:40,740 --> 00:30:41,787
you know, we can
avoid the chaos

555
00:30:41,860 --> 00:30:43,908
that happened in
the Icefall today.

556
00:30:44,540 --> 00:30:46,827
Adventure Consultants
are aiming for May 10.

557
00:30:46,900 --> 00:30:48,902
So are we, man!
Us too.

558
00:30:48,980 --> 00:30:50,186
May 10.

559
00:30:52,540 --> 00:30:55,430
Okay, that's bumper-to-bumper
traffic on the Hillary Step.

560
00:30:55,500 --> 00:30:56,581
Yes, it is,
that's my point.

561
00:30:56,660 --> 00:30:59,550
Look, this is ridiculous.
We're summiting when we want.

562
00:31:00,220 --> 00:31:01,220
All right?

563
00:31:01,260 --> 00:31:04,230
And I don't need
your permission to climb the mountain.

564
00:31:04,300 --> 00:31:06,382
Ian, have you seen
how many people are here at Base Camp?

565
00:31:06,460 --> 00:31:08,781
We're finished here.
Come on, guys.
Ian! Hey, man.

566
00:31:23,260 --> 00:31:24,910
Oh, Rob!

567
00:31:25,380 --> 00:31:28,065
- Ah! Come in, man!
- Hi.

568
00:31:28,860 --> 00:31:31,101
Have a drink, Rob!
Come on, man.

569
00:31:31,180 --> 00:31:32,864
<i>Na zdorovie.</i>

570
00:31:32,940 --> 00:31:34,271
<i>Na zdorovie!</i>

571
00:31:35,300 --> 00:31:37,348
Can we have a word?
Yeah.

572
00:31:42,940 --> 00:31:44,465
You feeling
a little crook, huh?

573
00:31:44,540 --> 00:31:45,951
No, it's just a little...

574
00:31:46,020 --> 00:31:47,749
Little touch of
the Delhi belly.

575
00:31:47,820 --> 00:31:49,231
He means
Buddha belly.

576
00:31:49,300 --> 00:31:50,950
Maybe Sandy's caviar.

577
00:31:51,020 --> 00:31:53,830
I told you not to have
the Dom Perignon with it!

578
00:31:53,900 --> 00:31:55,902
What's going on,
Roberto?

579
00:32:03,900 --> 00:32:07,268
I don't like the look
of the crowds on the ropes.

580
00:32:07,340 --> 00:32:08,780
I think we're gonna
have some trouble

581
00:32:08,820 --> 00:32:10,788
once we get
above Camp Three.

582
00:32:11,500 --> 00:32:13,180
I mean, you wanna top
it on the 10th, yeah?

583
00:32:13,220 --> 00:32:14,790
Yeah.
So do I.

584
00:32:16,580 --> 00:32:18,582
What, are you saying
we should team up?

585
00:32:18,660 --> 00:32:20,662
Well, it's an idea, yeah.

586
00:32:22,140 --> 00:32:23,585
Oh, man.

587
00:32:26,540 --> 00:32:29,430
I don't know, man.
We have different styles, man.

588
00:32:31,460 --> 00:32:35,431
All due respect, you're a hand-holder.
I mean, the best, but...

589
00:32:36,020 --> 00:32:38,341
I just believe that if you can't
get up there yourself

590
00:32:38,420 --> 00:32:40,900
you shouldn't be on
the mountain at all.

591
00:32:40,980 --> 00:32:43,870
You guide your team,
I guide mine.

592
00:32:43,940 --> 00:32:45,305
I'm just suggesting
that we work

593
00:32:45,380 --> 00:32:46,740
with each other
instead of against.

594
00:32:46,780 --> 00:32:49,511
The only way we both summit, mate,
is if we work together.

595
00:32:50,580 --> 00:32:52,742
Particularly fixing the ropes.

596
00:32:53,460 --> 00:32:55,349
It's gotta make sense.

597
00:33:00,820 --> 00:33:03,187
Whoo-ie! Why not?

598
00:33:04,460 --> 00:33:07,191
Yeah?
Yeah, I see the sense in it.

599
00:33:07,260 --> 00:33:09,103
Good man.
That was all.

600
00:33:09,180 --> 00:33:10,545
All right.

601
00:33:11,220 --> 00:33:14,030
Who's gonna lead
when we get up there?

602
00:33:18,420 --> 00:33:21,344
Rob. If I say I will
do it, it will be done.

603
00:33:26,540 --> 00:33:27,541
Whoa! Whoa!
Whoa! Whoa!

604
00:33:27,620 --> 00:33:28,621
You gotta work
with Ang Dorjee,

605
00:33:28,700 --> 00:33:30,589
because we're
working together now.

606
00:33:31,700 --> 00:33:33,862
I'm just saying,
if both of us...

607
00:33:33,940 --> 00:33:35,908
Whoa! Whoa!
Whoa! Whoa!

608
00:33:36,700 --> 00:33:37,826
Okay?

609
00:33:38,340 --> 00:33:39,705
Ang Dorjee.

610
00:33:41,620 --> 00:33:43,065
We're all professionals here.

611
00:33:43,180 --> 00:33:45,421
We'll work together and
we'll get the job done. Yes?

612
00:33:45,500 --> 00:33:46,547
All right.
Yeah.

613
00:33:46,620 --> 00:33:49,385
We're planning on stashing,
what, eight bottles of O

614
00:33:49,460 --> 00:33:50,700
up at the South Summit.

615
00:33:50,820 --> 00:33:52,940
- Well, I'm not using O.
- What do you mean?

616
00:33:52,980 --> 00:33:54,220
You're not
using oxygen at all?

617
00:33:54,300 --> 00:33:55,426
Come on, man.
You know you want to.

618
00:33:55,500 --> 00:33:56,945
English air.
Don't need it.

619
00:33:57,020 --> 00:33:59,227
Yeah, but Anatoli,
you're guiding for Scott this year.

620
00:33:59,300 --> 00:34:01,871
You have people's lives in your hands.
It's a job.

621
00:34:01,940 --> 00:34:04,511
Never used it.
Never will.

622
00:34:04,620 --> 00:34:06,907
Bigger problems
if you run out.

623
00:34:08,020 --> 00:34:09,021
Okay.

624
00:34:09,660 --> 00:34:11,071
I'll put some more
bottles of O up there.

625
00:34:11,180 --> 00:34:12,860
All right, that'll be good.
All right.

626
00:34:13,540 --> 00:34:14,701
Just so long as
you guys are clear.

627
00:34:14,780 --> 00:34:16,145
If you work for me,
you use oxygen,

628
00:34:16,220 --> 00:34:17,631
otherwise you
don't work for me.

629
00:34:17,700 --> 00:34:19,145
You don't have to
ask, mate.

630
00:34:19,260 --> 00:34:20,750
I've been up there
before without O's, Rob.

631
00:34:20,820 --> 00:34:22,345
I don't need to
do it with clients.

632
00:34:22,420 --> 00:34:24,582
All right, next
we have to fix ropes.

633
00:34:24,700 --> 00:34:27,180
Yeah.
Particularly above the Lhotse Face.

634
00:34:27,260 --> 00:34:29,149
Hillary Step need
new fixed rope.

635
00:34:29,220 --> 00:34:30,631
And South-East Ridge
as well.

636
00:34:30,700 --> 00:34:31,861
Yes, it does.
Well...

637
00:34:31,980 --> 00:34:33,345
My idea is that
we work together

638
00:34:33,420 --> 00:34:34,421
and we fix
ropes together.

639
00:34:34,500 --> 00:34:35,626
We share the duties.

640
00:34:35,700 --> 00:34:36,861
- Okay?
- Sounds good.

641
00:34:36,940 --> 00:34:38,590
All right,
you and Lopsang maybe get together.

642
00:34:38,660 --> 00:34:41,470
Talk about who wants
to fix what and where, okay?

643
00:34:42,140 --> 00:34:44,711
Only essentials. I'm not
gonna tell you what to pack,

644
00:34:44,780 --> 00:34:46,544
but be brutal. Okay?

645
00:34:46,660 --> 00:34:48,947
One pound down here
is like 10 up there.

646
00:34:50,180 --> 00:34:53,070
Light and fast.

647
00:34:53,140 --> 00:34:56,462
What, and just like that,
you kill my summit cappuccino.

648
00:34:57,500 --> 00:34:59,867
Go. go, go! Run!

649
00:34:59,980 --> 00:35:02,631
- That camera's totally dying.
- Okay.

650
00:35:02,700 --> 00:35:04,748
All right, it's gonna
be a tough week.

651
00:35:04,820 --> 00:35:08,142
But it is gonna be
the best Friday of your lives.

652
00:35:08,220 --> 00:35:10,461
Yeah, what are we
doing again on Friday?

653
00:35:10,540 --> 00:35:12,429
Summiting!

654
00:35:15,460 --> 00:35:17,269
- Now it's up to me, right?
- Yes, it is, yes, it is.

655
00:35:17,340 --> 00:35:18,387
I'll take three.

656
00:35:18,460 --> 00:35:19,700
It's from Jan.

657
00:35:22,460 --> 00:35:25,907
I knew it was gonna be a girl.
I can't believe it.

658
00:35:25,980 --> 00:35:26,981
It's a girl!

659
00:35:30,380 --> 00:35:32,109
All right,
good on you!

660
00:35:32,180 --> 00:35:33,545
I knew I was.

661
00:35:33,620 --> 00:35:34,621
I knew she was.
Congratulations.

662
00:35:34,700 --> 00:35:36,509
Thank you, thank you, Doug.
Cheers, mate.

663
00:35:37,300 --> 00:35:38,870
When's she due?

664
00:35:38,940 --> 00:35:40,465
Mid-July, as soon
as I get back.

665
00:35:40,540 --> 00:35:41,985
You better
sleep now, buddy.

666
00:35:42,060 --> 00:35:43,505
Yeah, that's true.

667
00:35:43,980 --> 00:35:45,470
Hey, Rob.

668
00:35:45,540 --> 00:35:46,871
Yeah?
So...

669
00:35:46,940 --> 00:35:48,385
Jan doesn't mind
you being here?

670
00:35:48,620 --> 00:35:49,621
Uh-oh.

671
00:35:49,860 --> 00:35:52,306
Krakauer's sword
is unleashed.

672
00:35:52,380 --> 00:35:54,986
It's okay. Jan's a climber, Jon,
she gets it.

673
00:35:55,060 --> 00:35:56,949
- Yeah!
- Cheers, Helen.

674
00:35:57,020 --> 00:35:58,590
What about you, Doug?
What about your wife?

675
00:35:58,660 --> 00:36:00,788
Oh, she's been fine with it,
ever since we divorced.

676
00:36:02,020 --> 00:36:03,260
She's been great
with everything since then.

677
00:36:03,340 --> 00:36:04,466
I'm so sorry, buddy.

678
00:36:04,540 --> 00:36:05,905
No, no.

679
00:36:05,980 --> 00:36:08,711
No, no, no, I ask
because Peach said to me,

680
00:36:08,780 --> 00:36:11,147
"if you climb one more mountain,
I will divorce you."

681
00:36:11,220 --> 00:36:14,303
And you went ahead
and then booked this trip!

682
00:36:15,140 --> 00:36:16,904
No, no, no,
the worst part of it

683
00:36:16,980 --> 00:36:20,189
is that I kind of
forgot to tell her.

684
00:36:21,860 --> 00:36:23,624
You don't forget to tell her
you're climbing Everest!

685
00:36:23,700 --> 00:36:24,667
I forgot to
tell her, I did.

686
00:36:24,740 --> 00:36:27,789
All right. It's all
on the table, here.

687
00:36:27,860 --> 00:36:32,104
It hurts, it's dangerous,
it destroys relationships,

688
00:36:32,180 --> 00:36:33,830
it's costing you
all a small fortune.

689
00:36:33,900 --> 00:36:35,470
Are there any
negative aspects to this game?

690
00:36:35,540 --> 00:36:38,669
I gotta ask the question,
you know I do.

691
00:36:38,740 --> 00:36:40,185
Why?

692
00:36:41,540 --> 00:36:42,701
Why.

693
00:36:44,340 --> 00:36:45,340
Because...

694
00:36:45,380 --> 00:36:47,064
It's there!

695
00:36:47,700 --> 00:36:49,668
That's why.
Thank you, Mr. Mallory.

696
00:36:49,780 --> 00:36:52,306
- Come on.
- Guys, I'm serious.

697
00:36:52,380 --> 00:36:55,270
Yasuko. Why are you
climbing Everest?

698
00:36:56,500 --> 00:36:57,501
Uh...

699
00:36:57,580 --> 00:36:59,503
I'm 47 years old,

700
00:36:59,580 --> 00:37:03,187
I have reached six of
the seven summits, so...

701
00:37:03,260 --> 00:37:06,901
Of course, now I have
to reach the seventh.

702
00:37:06,980 --> 00:37:08,550
That's not an answer.

703
00:37:09,100 --> 00:37:11,307
No. Why any summit?

704
00:37:11,380 --> 00:37:12,541
Doug.

705
00:37:12,620 --> 00:37:13,906
Me?
Why?

706
00:37:15,060 --> 00:37:16,027
Come on,
tell 'em about the kids.

707
00:37:16,100 --> 00:37:17,101
What?

708
00:37:17,180 --> 00:37:18,511
Tell 'em about the kids.

709
00:37:18,580 --> 00:37:19,991
Whose kids?
Oh...

710
00:37:20,060 --> 00:37:21,789
You have kids?

711
00:37:21,900 --> 00:37:24,380
Yeah, I have kids,
but, I thought I told you,

712
00:37:24,460 --> 00:37:26,940
there's an elementary school,
back home.

713
00:37:27,620 --> 00:37:29,622
And I've been going
and talking to the kids there

714
00:37:29,740 --> 00:37:33,187
and they actually helped me raise
some of the money to come

715
00:37:33,260 --> 00:37:36,548
and gave me a flag
to plant on the summit, and...

716
00:37:36,620 --> 00:37:39,703
So, I was thinking,
maybe it's...

717
00:37:39,780 --> 00:37:43,421
They see a
regular guy can,

718
00:37:43,500 --> 00:37:45,707
you know, follow
impossible dreams,

719
00:37:45,780 --> 00:37:47,623
maybe they'll be inspired

720
00:37:47,700 --> 00:37:49,702
to do the same, I guess.

721
00:37:50,460 --> 00:37:52,940
I'm climbing Mount Everest

722
00:37:54,780 --> 00:37:56,305
because I can.

723
00:37:57,100 --> 00:37:59,228
Because to be able
to climb that high

724
00:37:59,300 --> 00:38:02,463
and see that kind of beauty
that nobody ever sees,

725
00:38:03,580 --> 00:38:05,742
it'd be a crime not to.

726
00:38:07,300 --> 00:38:08,347
Hear, hear, Dougie.

727
00:38:08,420 --> 00:38:10,309
- There you go.
- I like that.

728
00:38:15,820 --> 00:38:16,901
Hello?

729
00:38:16,980 --> 00:38:18,823
<i>Hey. Did I wake you?</i>

730
00:38:19,940 --> 00:38:21,101
No.

731
00:38:21,660 --> 00:38:23,583
<i>I did too, you liar.</i>

732
00:38:24,140 --> 00:38:25,187
<i>Huh?</i>

733
00:38:26,980 --> 00:38:28,823
<i>You okay?</i>
Yeah.

734
00:38:29,380 --> 00:38:31,030
Yeah, yeah,
I'm good, I'm better.

735
00:38:31,100 --> 00:38:32,465
I'm better now, I'm...

736
00:38:33,020 --> 00:38:34,351
<i>I miss you.</i>

737
00:38:35,620 --> 00:38:38,146
<i>We go for
the final ascent tomorrow.</i>

738
00:38:38,660 --> 00:38:41,106
So, you summit Friday?

739
00:38:41,180 --> 00:38:42,750
<i>Yeah, the 10th.</i>

740
00:38:43,580 --> 00:38:44,741
<i>It's your lucky day.</i>

741
00:38:44,820 --> 00:38:46,026
It is.

742
00:38:46,860 --> 00:38:48,510
<i>How's the weather?</i>

743
00:38:49,020 --> 00:38:50,545
It's good.

744
00:38:50,620 --> 00:38:52,622
Yeah, I think we're
gonna get a good window.

745
00:38:53,220 --> 00:38:55,461
<i>So, it's a girl.</i>

746
00:38:55,540 --> 00:38:56,780
Yeah.

747
00:38:56,860 --> 00:38:59,670
And did you go to the doctor,
did you get a scan done?

748
00:38:59,740 --> 00:39:00,787
Did you see her?

749
00:39:00,860 --> 00:39:02,146
<i>Yeah, sure did.</i>

750
00:39:04,060 --> 00:39:07,109
And? Come on.
What did she look like?

751
00:39:07,180 --> 00:39:09,990
Oh, you know.
Blonde hair, nice smile,

752
00:39:10,060 --> 00:39:11,107
perfect
height-to-weight ratio,

753
00:39:11,180 --> 00:39:14,024
she's gonna be a great climber.

754
00:39:15,220 --> 00:39:16,870
<i>She's there, Rob.</i>

755
00:39:17,380 --> 00:39:19,747
<i>Already.</i>
Wow.

756
00:39:20,180 --> 00:39:21,784
<i>A little me, a little you.</i>

757
00:39:21,860 --> 00:39:23,385
A little bear, huh?

758
00:39:25,220 --> 00:39:27,791
<i>And then, one day, you</i>

759
00:39:27,900 --> 00:39:29,231
and me

760
00:39:30,220 --> 00:39:31,220
and our little Sarah,

761
00:39:31,260 --> 00:39:33,308
we'll all go climbing
together. Hmm?

762
00:39:33,380 --> 00:39:34,620
Sarah?

763
00:39:35,700 --> 00:39:37,702
<i>Yeah, what do you think?</i>

764
00:39:37,780 --> 00:39:39,828
No way!
<i>Come on.</i>

765
00:39:39,900 --> 00:39:40,901
No!

766
00:39:40,980 --> 00:39:42,311
<i>Please? Think about it.</i>

767
00:39:42,380 --> 00:39:43,711
No.
<i>Huh?</i>

768
00:39:48,380 --> 00:39:49,666
<i>You still there?</i>

769
00:39:49,740 --> 00:39:51,788
Of course I'm still here.

770
00:39:54,460 --> 00:39:55,746
I love you.

771
00:39:56,580 --> 00:39:58,150
<i>Love you, too.</i>

772
00:40:02,740 --> 00:40:04,344
<i>Sleep well, my love.</i>

773
00:40:04,420 --> 00:40:06,388
All right. Bye.

774
00:41:21,860 --> 00:41:24,784
Take it easy, now.
You're gonna be okay.

775
00:41:24,860 --> 00:41:27,101
We're gonna get you
down the hill. All right?

776
00:41:27,180 --> 00:41:28,625
Hey, Neal, you okay?

777
00:41:28,700 --> 00:41:30,509
Yeah, Dale, he doesn't
look too good.

778
00:41:31,460 --> 00:41:32,460
We need to
take him down.

779
00:41:32,500 --> 00:41:33,945
Yeah.

780
00:41:34,020 --> 00:41:35,943
You can't get
Scott on the radio?

781
00:41:36,020 --> 00:41:38,466
Nope. Nah, I think
he's up ahead.

782
00:41:48,780 --> 00:41:50,623
Best not to stare
too long at the summit.

783
00:41:50,700 --> 00:41:52,941
That's a long way
to go, man.

784
00:41:55,380 --> 00:41:58,623
Head down,
one step at a time.

785
00:41:58,700 --> 00:42:00,384
You got it, boss.

786
00:42:03,180 --> 00:42:04,784
You seen Dale?

787
00:42:04,860 --> 00:42:07,670
Yeah, I did, he wasn't
looking too good

788
00:42:07,740 --> 00:42:10,983
but Neal seemed to have
a handle on the situation.

789
00:42:11,060 --> 00:42:12,061
Tried to get you
on the radio.

790
00:42:12,140 --> 00:42:14,063
You're kidding me.
No.

791
00:42:15,100 --> 00:42:17,262
This thing's
not working, huh?

792
00:42:18,220 --> 00:42:19,631
I'm going down to Camp One.

793
00:42:19,740 --> 00:42:21,629
If he's not doing so well,
I'm gonna take him down to Base Camp

794
00:42:21,740 --> 00:42:24,471
and I'll head back up.
You guys all right?

795
00:42:24,540 --> 00:42:25,780
Yeah.

796
00:42:27,220 --> 00:42:29,188
He can't be too far
ahead of you, mate.

797
00:42:29,260 --> 00:42:32,070
Yeah, I'll make it
down in half the time.

798
00:42:33,100 --> 00:42:34,909
I'm gonna
catch you! Whoo!

799
00:42:52,700 --> 00:42:53,700
Rob to Guy.

800
00:42:53,740 --> 00:42:56,186
<i>Rob to Guy,
you up there, mate?</i>

801
00:42:56,260 --> 00:42:58,740
Yeah, Guy to Rob.
I'm here.

802
00:42:58,860 --> 00:42:59,907
<i>Good to
hear you, Gee.</i>

803
00:43:00,620 --> 00:43:02,304
<i>Where are you?</i>

804
00:43:02,380 --> 00:43:04,269
Camp One, Pumori.

805
00:43:04,340 --> 00:43:05,546
Yeah.

806
00:43:06,540 --> 00:43:09,111
There you go, I got
the old sly rotter.

807
00:43:09,180 --> 00:43:11,706
Listen, I think you're on
the wrong mountain, there.

808
00:43:12,620 --> 00:43:14,702
Look, I can't talk,
we gotta get out of here.

809
00:43:14,780 --> 00:43:15,780
<i>All right, mate.</i>

810
00:43:15,820 --> 00:43:18,027
<i>Well, listen,
you take care on the kiddie slope.</i>

811
00:43:18,100 --> 00:43:19,704
<i>I'm gonna get back
to the real thing.</i>

812
00:43:19,780 --> 00:43:22,943
<i>Yeah, don't worry, Rob.
I'll keep an eye on you.</i>

813
00:43:31,940 --> 00:43:32,941
Ice!

814
00:43:37,820 --> 00:43:38,867
Rob!

815
00:43:40,140 --> 00:43:41,551
I got you!

816
00:43:51,980 --> 00:43:53,311
Harold, you okay?

817
00:43:57,140 --> 00:43:58,744
Is everyone okay?

818
00:43:58,820 --> 00:44:00,424
We're okay!

819
00:44:05,660 --> 00:44:07,583
Come here, sit down, sit.

820
00:44:07,660 --> 00:44:08,866
I'm fine.

821
00:44:10,500 --> 00:44:11,786
Look at me.

822
00:44:11,860 --> 00:44:13,100
Look at me.
I'm fine, mate.

823
00:44:13,180 --> 00:44:14,227
Look at me, Harold!

824
00:44:14,300 --> 00:44:15,825
Look, I'm telling you,
I'm all right.

825
00:44:15,900 --> 00:44:17,709
Okay.
I'm all right.

826
00:44:20,140 --> 00:44:21,301
There you go.
Thank you.

827
00:44:21,980 --> 00:44:24,347
Don't do that
to me again, eh?

828
00:44:25,540 --> 00:44:26,905
I'm sorry.

829
00:44:28,020 --> 00:44:29,101
Okay, mate.

830
00:44:29,180 --> 00:44:30,181
I'm gonna drop
back with Frank,

831
00:44:30,260 --> 00:44:32,308
he's struggling a bit,
all right?

832
00:44:32,380 --> 00:44:33,791
All right.

833
00:44:37,820 --> 00:44:38,821
Straight down.

834
00:44:39,820 --> 00:44:41,549
Let's get him
on the oxygen.

835
00:44:41,620 --> 00:44:43,145
Rob Hall to Scott Fischer,
Rob Hall to Scott Fischer,

836
00:44:43,220 --> 00:44:44,540
Mountain Madness,
how do you copy?

837
00:44:45,260 --> 00:44:47,661
Hey, man! Scott, here.

838
00:44:48,260 --> 00:44:50,831
I've been down to Base Camp,
and I'm back at Camp One.

839
00:44:50,900 --> 00:44:52,470
I'm gonna catch you tomorrow.

840
00:44:52,540 --> 00:44:55,020
What, you're not gonna
rest up a day first? No?

841
00:44:56,220 --> 00:44:57,790
<i>Scott, you sound
a little rough.</i>

842
00:44:58,580 --> 00:45:00,150
<i>Mate, take an extra day.</i>

843
00:45:00,220 --> 00:45:03,144
No way, José, what,
miss out on all the fun?

844
00:45:03,860 --> 00:45:07,182
That's a lot of up and down in one day,
even for you, Scott.

845
00:45:07,260 --> 00:45:09,388
You know what
they say, man.

846
00:45:10,220 --> 00:45:13,064
It's not the altitude,
it's the attitude.

847
00:45:14,580 --> 00:45:16,708
<i>Are you sure
you're gonna be okay?</i>

848
00:45:16,780 --> 00:45:17,906
<i>Scott?</i>
I'll be good.

849
00:45:17,980 --> 00:45:20,745
Just taking a shot
of dexamethasone now.

850
00:45:21,700 --> 00:45:25,421
<i>Well, just don't push yourself
too hard, okay? Over and out.</i>

851
00:45:32,260 --> 00:45:35,821
Rob, I've just been over
to Mal's to get a weather update.

852
00:45:35,900 --> 00:45:37,664
It's moving fast.

853
00:45:37,740 --> 00:45:40,266
It's changed
course slightly.

854
00:45:41,260 --> 00:45:44,264
<i>And it could still go north,
but, if it doesn't</i>

855
00:45:44,340 --> 00:45:48,026
<i>it's gonna hit sometime
on the 11th, I reckon.</i>

856
00:45:50,700 --> 00:45:52,941
It's a weather
forecast, Helen.

857
00:45:53,020 --> 00:45:54,943
This mountain makes
its own weather.

858
00:45:55,020 --> 00:45:56,101
We're keeping an eye on it.

859
00:45:57,340 --> 00:45:59,422
<i>Yeah, sure, just
letting you know.</i>

860
00:45:59,540 --> 00:46:01,110
Appreciate it, Helen.

861
00:46:03,860 --> 00:46:05,783
Why do we do
this to ourselves?

862
00:46:10,300 --> 00:46:11,790
Oh, this is crazy.

863
00:46:17,460 --> 00:46:19,462
You know, I never
told Krakauer this

864
00:46:19,540 --> 00:46:21,781
when he was asking us
why we climb Everest.

865
00:46:22,540 --> 00:46:24,144
When I'm at home

866
00:46:25,780 --> 00:46:27,544
I just got this big,

867
00:46:28,980 --> 00:46:31,381
black cloud following me.

868
00:46:31,460 --> 00:46:33,588
You know,
like a depression?

869
00:46:34,860 --> 00:46:36,510
And when I'm out here

870
00:46:36,620 --> 00:46:37,860
on a mountain,
any mountain...

871
00:46:37,940 --> 00:46:39,180
Yeah?

872
00:46:40,780 --> 00:46:42,862
It's just like it's a cure.

873
00:46:44,620 --> 00:46:46,509
I feel like I'm reborn.

874
00:46:46,980 --> 00:46:49,062
So, you're happy now?

875
00:46:50,660 --> 00:46:52,742
No, I'm starting
to wonder.

876
00:46:55,500 --> 00:46:57,343
This is suffering, man.

877
00:46:58,980 --> 00:47:00,903
Yeah.
This is suffering.

878
00:47:01,020 --> 00:47:02,351
Yeah.

879
00:47:03,180 --> 00:47:05,581
Suffer a few more days,

880
00:47:05,660 --> 00:47:07,185
for the rest of your
life you'll be a guy

881
00:47:07,260 --> 00:47:09,501
that got to the top
of Everest.

882
00:47:09,740 --> 00:47:11,583
Mmm.
Huh?

883
00:47:14,860 --> 00:47:17,022
I just hope I get there.

884
00:47:17,700 --> 00:47:19,065
Yeah.

885
00:47:20,540 --> 00:47:23,066
Just hope I get there,
and get home.

886
00:47:29,380 --> 00:47:31,109
What do you
think, Mike?

887
00:47:33,980 --> 00:47:35,470
Looks pretty good.

888
00:47:35,540 --> 00:47:38,146
Little bit of wind,
up higher.

889
00:47:38,220 --> 00:47:40,382
I mean, if it picks up,
we can always come back down.

890
00:47:40,460 --> 00:47:42,701
Exactly.
It's your call, Rob.

891
00:47:43,820 --> 00:47:46,391
Let's get 'em all going.

892
00:48:40,860 --> 00:48:41,861
Rob!

893
00:48:41,940 --> 00:48:43,101
You okay?

894
00:48:43,820 --> 00:48:45,106
Not good!

895
00:48:48,740 --> 00:48:49,741
Ah.

896
00:48:50,740 --> 00:48:53,789
I'm hoping it's gonna
die down after sundown.

897
00:48:53,860 --> 00:48:55,828
It's been doing that.

898
00:48:55,900 --> 00:48:57,470
I don't like this.

899
00:48:57,540 --> 00:49:00,623
Well, we don't go
if it doesn't calm.

900
00:49:00,700 --> 00:49:02,907
I talk to Scott
when he comes here.

901
00:49:02,980 --> 00:49:03,981
Okay.

902
00:49:17,300 --> 00:49:19,462
Scott! Scott!

903
00:49:19,540 --> 00:49:21,110
Toli?
Here!

904
00:49:31,940 --> 00:49:32,940
Toli!

905
00:49:32,980 --> 00:49:35,631
Where's Rob?
Where are they?

906
00:49:35,700 --> 00:49:37,031
We go down!
No.

907
00:49:37,700 --> 00:49:40,783
What's Rob's...
What's Rob's team doing?

908
00:49:41,500 --> 00:49:44,822
He wants to see
if this passes.

909
00:49:45,700 --> 00:49:47,190
If he waits,

910
00:49:50,220 --> 00:49:51,381
we wait.

911
00:49:51,460 --> 00:49:52,541
Okay.

912
00:50:06,500 --> 00:50:07,990
Hey, guys.

913
00:50:08,580 --> 00:50:10,582
Come out and take a look.

914
00:50:24,700 --> 00:50:27,180
At least somebody
up there loves us.

915
00:50:27,260 --> 00:50:28,546
Nothing?

916
00:50:32,260 --> 00:50:34,342
Where'd the storm go?

917
00:50:34,740 --> 00:50:36,230
Exactly.

918
00:50:37,100 --> 00:50:38,704
That's crazy.

919
00:50:38,820 --> 00:50:40,743
You ready to saddle up?

920
00:50:43,060 --> 00:50:46,189
Okay, everyone.
We got a window.

921
00:50:47,420 --> 00:50:49,582
We don't know
how long it's gonna last,

922
00:50:49,660 --> 00:50:51,867
but we're gonna
go for it.

923
00:50:51,940 --> 00:50:53,829
Be ready in
half an hour.

924
00:50:53,900 --> 00:50:55,140
We'll have
a 2:00 p.m. turnaround,

925
00:50:55,220 --> 00:50:56,460
let's climb this thing.

926
00:50:56,540 --> 00:50:57,666
Okay.

927
00:51:01,980 --> 00:51:04,062
So, today's
the day, huh?

928
00:51:04,780 --> 00:51:06,020
Yep.

929
00:51:07,740 --> 00:51:09,265
Now or never.

930
00:51:12,460 --> 00:51:14,030
Oh, boy.

931
00:51:17,420 --> 00:51:19,900
Now the South Africans
were late out of Camp Three.

932
00:51:19,980 --> 00:51:22,108
They never made
it into Camp Four.

933
00:51:22,180 --> 00:51:23,909
Probably got caught up in it.

934
00:51:23,980 --> 00:51:25,709
<i>Maybe it blew through early.</i>

935
00:51:25,780 --> 00:51:28,226
Yeah, well,
it hit us all night,

936
00:51:28,300 --> 00:51:31,110
but now there's nothing.
Absolutely nothing.

937
00:51:31,180 --> 00:51:33,387
So, it's definitely
worth a shot.

938
00:51:33,500 --> 00:51:36,310
<i>I'll radio out and
tell everyone the news.</i>

939
00:51:37,180 --> 00:51:38,670
<i>Any messages?</i>

940
00:51:39,340 --> 00:51:42,469
Yeah, ring Jan
and tell her that we're heading out.

941
00:51:42,540 --> 00:51:44,269
I'll call you,
Helen, in 12 hours

942
00:51:44,340 --> 00:51:45,910
when we get
to the summit.

943
00:51:45,980 --> 00:51:47,789
Turnaround's 2:00 p.m.

944
00:51:47,860 --> 00:51:49,783
<i>Good luck,
and Godspeed to you all.</i>

945
00:51:49,860 --> 00:51:51,669
Okay, thanks,
Helen. Bye-bye.

946
00:51:51,740 --> 00:51:52,866
I'll see you
guys up there.

947
00:51:52,940 --> 00:51:54,021
- Take it easy, Scott.
- Let's do it.

948
00:51:54,100 --> 00:51:56,387
Gonna get a couple hours of sleep,
and I'll be right behind you.

949
00:51:56,460 --> 00:51:57,461
- Yeah, okay.
- See you at the top.

950
00:51:57,540 --> 00:51:58,587
Have fun, Pittman.

951
00:51:58,660 --> 00:52:00,503
You get some
rest, okay?

952
00:52:00,580 --> 00:52:01,580
See you there.

953
00:52:01,620 --> 00:52:03,384
You got the ropes
for the Hillary Step?

954
00:52:03,460 --> 00:52:04,586
Yeah.

955
00:52:04,660 --> 00:52:05,991
Okay.
Okay.

956
00:52:06,060 --> 00:52:07,903
Okay. Yeah.

957
00:52:24,180 --> 00:52:26,023
Can we go
any faster?

958
00:52:26,100 --> 00:52:29,309
Not a chance we can go faster here.
It's too difficult.

959
00:52:29,380 --> 00:52:31,382
This could take a while.

960
00:52:32,300 --> 00:52:34,064
We're losing time.

961
00:53:00,420 --> 00:53:02,502
Beck. What's wrong?

962
00:53:02,580 --> 00:53:04,070
I don't know.

963
00:53:06,820 --> 00:53:10,222
I had an operation a couple years ago,
on my eyes.

964
00:53:10,300 --> 00:53:11,586
That might be it.

965
00:53:12,260 --> 00:53:14,501
- I don't know.
- Okay.

966
00:53:15,580 --> 00:53:17,423
You guys go
in front of us.

967
00:53:17,500 --> 00:53:20,549
All right, Beck,
let's sit you down.

968
00:53:26,220 --> 00:53:28,382
Beck. Look at me.

969
00:53:30,860 --> 00:53:31,941
I need to send you
down with someone.

970
00:53:32,020 --> 00:53:33,220
No, I don't wanna
go down, Rob.

971
00:53:33,300 --> 00:53:36,588
No, you gotta go down.
I don't wanna go down.

972
00:53:39,740 --> 00:53:40,946
Okay.

973
00:53:43,820 --> 00:53:46,790
Right, Beck, listen.

974
00:53:46,860 --> 00:53:49,147
You can wait here for half an hour.
Beck, listen to me.

975
00:53:49,260 --> 00:53:50,591
If it gets
better by then

976
00:53:51,180 --> 00:53:53,660
join in the queue
and keep going up.

977
00:53:54,300 --> 00:53:56,667
But if it doesn't get better, Beck,
I'm sorry, mate, it's over.

978
00:53:56,740 --> 00:53:57,741
Okay.

979
00:53:57,820 --> 00:53:59,026
The Sherpas are
gonna go up and drop off

980
00:53:59,100 --> 00:54:00,590
the extra oxygen
at the South Summit

981
00:54:01,380 --> 00:54:03,189
then I'm gonna send
one of them down for you.

982
00:54:03,300 --> 00:54:05,109
Is that clear?
Yeah?
Mmm-hmm.

983
00:54:06,900 --> 00:54:08,345
Okay, mate.

984
00:54:08,420 --> 00:54:09,785
All right.

985
00:54:13,580 --> 00:54:15,025
See you.

986
00:54:16,140 --> 00:54:18,381
Sandy, do
you want to go down?

987
00:54:18,460 --> 00:54:20,701
What? No. No way.

988
00:54:20,780 --> 00:54:22,862
Look, Lopsang,
I'm gonna make it to the top.

989
00:54:22,940 --> 00:54:23,941
Do you understand?

990
00:54:24,900 --> 00:54:26,470
Okay.
I'm not going back.

991
00:54:26,540 --> 00:54:28,429
Okay?
Okay,

992
00:54:40,460 --> 00:54:41,791
Where are the ropes?

993
00:54:41,860 --> 00:54:44,340
There is no rope!
No rope.

994
00:54:44,420 --> 00:54:45,751
Yeah, they
should have been fixed.

995
00:54:45,860 --> 00:54:47,749
Do you have more
in your pack?

996
00:54:47,860 --> 00:54:50,511
Lopsang
has the rope. He's not here!

997
00:54:50,580 --> 00:54:52,628
Harold. No ropes?

998
00:54:52,740 --> 00:54:53,787
No.

999
00:54:54,980 --> 00:54:56,027
Neal.

1000
00:54:56,100 --> 00:54:57,147
Hey, Rob.

1001
00:54:58,180 --> 00:54:59,750
Listen, we got
a problem, here, mate.

1002
00:54:59,820 --> 00:55:03,461
There's no fixed ropes on the
traverse to the Hillary Step, over.

1003
00:55:03,540 --> 00:55:04,780
<i>Where's Ang
Dorjee and Lopsang?</i>

1004
00:55:04,860 --> 00:55:06,271
Yeah, I've got
Ang Dorjee here,

1005
00:55:06,380 --> 00:55:07,905
but there's no
sign of Lopsang.

1006
00:55:07,980 --> 00:55:10,665
So me, Neal,
and Toli are gonna

1007
00:55:10,740 --> 00:55:12,469
have to set some
new ones, over.

1008
00:55:12,540 --> 00:55:13,740
- Find them?
- Yeah.

1009
00:55:13,780 --> 00:55:15,669
Good.
Let's do it!

1010
00:55:20,500 --> 00:55:22,104
What's going on?

1011
00:55:22,180 --> 00:55:23,830
No fixed ropes.

1012
00:55:23,940 --> 00:55:24,987
What?

1013
00:55:54,380 --> 00:55:55,905
That's it.

