Rob, I've got
Jan for you.

1508
01:30:50,700 --> 01:30:52,225
<i>My Jan?</i>

1509
01:30:52,300 --> 01:30:53,301
Yeah, she's just here.

1510
01:30:53,380 --> 01:30:54,711
Jan, you're on.

1511
01:30:54,780 --> 01:30:55,941
<i>Okay.</i>

1512
01:30:56,940 --> 01:30:59,341
<i>Hi, sweetheart,
how are you doing?</i>

1513
01:31:02,820 --> 01:31:04,345
Hi, my love.

1514
01:31:04,420 --> 01:31:05,421
I'm a bit...

1515
01:31:05,940 --> 01:31:07,271
<i>A bit cold</i>

1516
01:31:08,420 --> 01:31:10,229
<i>but I'm okay.</i>

1517
01:31:10,300 --> 01:31:12,029
I know you are.

1518
01:31:12,100 --> 01:31:14,307
<i>But the sun'll
warm you soon.</i>

1519
01:31:15,180 --> 01:31:16,227
<i>Sweetheart?</i>

1520
01:31:16,980 --> 01:31:18,903
<i>You've gotta get moving.</i>

1521
01:31:19,460 --> 01:31:21,986
<i>You've gotta come on down.</i>

1522
01:31:22,740 --> 01:31:24,185
<i>My hands</i>

1523
01:31:27,140 --> 01:31:28,505
<i>are frozen.</i>

1524
01:31:31,820 --> 01:31:33,629
My feet are frozen.

1525
01:31:34,980 --> 01:31:38,302
<i>We're sending people
up to you with tea and O's.</i>

1526
01:31:38,380 --> 01:31:41,589
But you've gotta get moving.
Rob? Can you hear me?

1527
01:31:42,180 --> 01:31:44,501
<i>You've gotta get
your circulation going.</i>

1528
01:31:44,580 --> 01:31:46,150
Okay, my love.

1529
01:31:46,860 --> 01:31:49,864
You do it...
You do it right now.

1530
01:31:52,420 --> 01:31:53,831
I love you.

1531
01:31:55,140 --> 01:31:56,426
Over and out.

1532
01:32:06,860 --> 01:32:08,544
Come on, Rob.

1533
01:32:58,660 --> 01:33:00,469
We can't carry them.

1534
01:33:02,100 --> 01:33:03,909
It's not possible.

1535
01:33:03,980 --> 01:33:04,981
It's gonna...

1536
01:33:07,220 --> 01:33:09,188
It's gonna take all we got

1537
01:33:09,260 --> 01:33:11,342
just to get
ourselves down.

1538
01:33:13,580 --> 01:33:15,423
I don't wanna die, man.

1539
01:33:19,980 --> 01:33:22,506
<i>Helen, it's Mike here.
Do you copy?</i>

1540
01:33:23,740 --> 01:33:25,390
Come in, Mike.
What do you got?

1541
01:33:25,460 --> 01:33:28,350
Yasuko and Beck

1542
01:33:28,420 --> 01:33:30,627
did not make it
back to camp.

1543
01:33:35,460 --> 01:33:38,748
Okay, Mike. Thanks
for letting us know.

1544
01:34:12,820 --> 01:34:14,106
Meg?

1545
01:34:17,020 --> 01:34:18,146
Bub?

1546
01:34:51,060 --> 01:34:52,744
Helen Base Camp.
Helen Base Camp.

1547
01:34:53,620 --> 01:34:55,224
<i>Helen Base Camp.</i>

1548
01:34:56,340 --> 01:34:58,149
Ang Dorjee,
this is Helen.

1549
01:34:58,220 --> 01:34:59,824
<i>We have to turn back!</i>

1550
01:35:00,460 --> 01:35:02,542
<i>There is a very
bad storm again.</i>

1551
01:35:04,380 --> 01:35:06,382
Your call, Ang Dorjee.
<i>Sorry.</i>

1552
01:35:06,460 --> 01:35:09,430
We'll try to again
when the storm's passed.

1553
01:35:09,500 --> 01:35:12,788
<i>We'll leave some tea
and oxygen here. Sorry.</i>

1554
01:35:19,980 --> 01:35:22,108
We have to tell Rob
they're not coming.

1555
01:35:23,860 --> 01:35:25,225
Okay.

1556
01:35:34,380 --> 01:35:35,506
<i>Hey, Rob,
it's Guy, mate.</i>

1557
01:35:35,580 --> 01:35:36,866
Guy.

1558
01:35:38,820 --> 01:35:41,630
Can't stop shaking, mate.

1559
01:35:42,860 --> 01:35:45,784
<i>The boys have hit
a bit of high wind.</i>

1560
01:35:45,900 --> 01:35:48,824
<i>And your best shot is
gonna be to get lower.</i>

1561
01:35:51,580 --> 01:35:53,389
Let me think about it.

1562
01:35:56,020 --> 01:35:58,864
<i>I think I can hang
out here another night.</i>

1563
01:36:04,260 --> 01:36:06,740
We'll try again
first thing, okay?

1564
01:37:15,500 --> 01:37:18,026
Helen?
<i>Yeah.</i>

1565
01:37:18,700 --> 01:37:20,748
<i>Yeah, he's still there.</i>

1566
01:37:21,740 --> 01:37:24,186
He's just below
the South Summit.

1567
01:37:24,860 --> 01:37:29,468
He's got oxygen,
but it's iced up.

1568
01:37:29,540 --> 01:37:32,623
<i>We don't know whether
he's been able to free it.</i>

1569
01:37:34,820 --> 01:37:36,788
Is anybody with him?

1570
01:37:36,860 --> 01:37:38,305
<i>No.</i>

1571
01:37:38,860 --> 01:37:40,146
<i>No.</i>

1572
01:37:41,020 --> 01:37:42,181
<i>You have to get
him down before dark.</i>

1573
01:37:42,260 --> 01:37:44,388
<i>He won't survive
another night.</i>

1574
01:37:44,460 --> 01:37:45,700
We know.

1575
01:37:47,220 --> 01:37:50,144
But the storm's
come back, real bad.

1576
01:37:51,660 --> 01:37:54,550
<i>We can't get anyone
up to him tonight.</i>

1577
01:37:54,620 --> 01:37:55,906
<i>We tried.</i>

1578
01:37:59,740 --> 01:38:02,061
He might as well
be on the moon.

1579
01:38:04,740 --> 01:38:05,741
Uh...

1580
01:38:08,060 --> 01:38:10,506
<i>Can you put me
on with him again?</i>

1581
01:38:10,580 --> 01:38:11,911
Of course.

1582
01:38:15,220 --> 01:38:17,268
Guy, get Rob.

1583
01:38:21,700 --> 01:38:23,270
Hey, Rob,
it's Guy.

1584
01:38:24,740 --> 01:38:26,708
<i>I've got Jan for you.</i>

1585
01:38:27,420 --> 01:38:31,106
Hold on.
Give me a sec.

1586
01:38:45,780 --> 01:38:46,906
<i>Okay.</i>

1587
01:38:55,900 --> 01:38:57,470
<i>Hi, sweetheart.</i>

1588
01:38:58,860 --> 01:39:00,464
<i>How are you?</i>

1589
01:39:03,220 --> 01:39:05,541
I'm thinking about you.

1590
01:39:09,460 --> 01:39:11,110
You sound good.

1591
01:39:13,780 --> 01:39:15,623
<i>Are you warm, my love?</i>

1592
01:39:16,700 --> 01:39:19,067
I might have
a little frostbite.

1593
01:39:21,420 --> 01:39:24,344
I'm looking forward to
making it all better.

1594
01:39:27,300 --> 01:39:29,462
<i>I can't wait for you
to come home.</i>

1595
01:39:32,820 --> 01:39:34,185
<i>How's Sarah?</i>

1596
01:39:35,140 --> 01:39:36,505
Sarah?

1597
01:39:37,420 --> 01:39:38,785
<i>Yeah.</i>

1598
01:39:40,460 --> 01:39:42,349
Yeah, Sarah's good.

1599
01:39:44,180 --> 01:39:46,786
<i>Will you call her that
for me?</i>

1600
01:39:47,180 --> 01:39:48,909
<i>Yes, I will.</i>

1601
01:39:51,660 --> 01:39:54,664
I don't think
I'm gonna get to meet her.

1602
01:39:58,260 --> 01:40:00,103
<i>I'm so sorry.</i>

1603
01:40:04,940 --> 01:40:06,510
Don't say that.

1604
01:40:08,860 --> 01:40:11,181
If anyone can
make it, you can.

1605
01:40:11,260 --> 01:40:12,785
<i>Remember?</i>

1606
01:40:17,100 --> 01:40:18,545
I love you.

1607
01:40:20,340 --> 01:40:22,866
Please don't worry too much.

1608
01:40:29,220 --> 01:40:31,268
<i>Good night, my love.</i>

1609
01:40:44,980 --> 01:40:46,903
I love you, Rob.

1610
01:40:51,060 --> 01:40:52,585
<i>I love you.</i>

1611
01:44:16,580 --> 01:44:18,105
Beck?

1612
01:44:21,260 --> 01:44:23,183
<i>Helen,
it's Mike here.</i>

1613
01:44:23,780 --> 01:44:25,544
<i>Helen, do you copy?</i>

1614
01:44:26,100 --> 01:44:27,704
Mike, come in.

1615
01:44:27,780 --> 01:44:29,544
<i>Beck's still alive.</i>

1616
01:44:29,620 --> 01:44:31,782
<i>He walked himself into camp.</i>

1617
01:44:31,860 --> 01:44:34,022
<i>David Breashears
and the IMAX team</i>

1618
01:44:34,100 --> 01:44:36,262
<i>are gonna get him
down to Camp One.</i>

1619
01:44:38,700 --> 01:44:40,190
Thanks, Mike.

1620
01:44:44,180 --> 01:44:47,502
<i>We don't even
know how, but he is alive.</i>

1621
01:44:48,500 --> 01:44:49,626
<i>The thing is, Peach,</i>

1622
01:44:50,340 --> 01:44:52,104
we can't get him
down the Icefall.

1623
01:44:52,180 --> 01:44:53,466
<i>Oh, no, I'll
get him down.</i>

1624
01:44:53,540 --> 01:44:55,747
I'll get him down. Okay.

1625
01:44:55,820 --> 01:44:58,744
Okay, what do we need?
We need a helicopter, right?

1626
01:44:58,820 --> 01:45:01,585
Yeah, but they can't take
a helicopter up that high

1627
01:45:01,660 --> 01:45:03,344
because the air is too thin.

1628
01:45:03,900 --> 01:45:06,744
<i>We should try,
but it is one heck of a risk.</i>

1629
01:45:06,820 --> 01:45:08,584
And he's not in
a good way, Peach,

1630
01:45:08,660 --> 01:45:10,867
so I don't want you to get
your hopes up too high.

1631
01:45:16,500 --> 01:45:18,229
One step at a time.

1632
01:45:21,540 --> 01:45:22,746
You gotta keep moving.
Tired.

1633
01:45:22,820 --> 01:45:23,901
I know.
I'm tired.

1634
01:45:24,020 --> 01:45:26,022
I know you are. Come on.

1635
01:45:28,340 --> 01:45:29,990
Slow and steady.

1636
01:45:31,660 --> 01:45:34,027
Come on,
keep moving.

1637
01:45:34,100 --> 01:45:35,590
Yes, I'd like
the number

1638
01:45:35,660 --> 01:45:38,345
of the American Embassy
in Kathmandu, Nepal.

1639
01:45:38,980 --> 01:45:41,267
Yes, Nepal.
Ambassador, please.

1640
01:45:41,340 --> 01:45:42,785
No, sweets,
I can't hold.

1641
01:45:42,860 --> 01:45:45,306
No, you listen, sir,
my husband's already died once

1642
01:45:45,380 --> 01:45:46,791
as you'll have
seen on the news.

1643
01:45:46,860 --> 01:45:48,340
Trust me, having him
die a second time

1644
01:45:48,380 --> 01:45:50,747
is not gonna
play well on CNN.

1645
01:45:51,380 --> 01:45:53,109
There we go, buddy.

1646
01:45:54,180 --> 01:45:56,103
That's it, all right.

1647
01:46:01,340 --> 01:46:02,341
Mike.

1648
01:46:02,420 --> 01:46:03,421
Mmm-hmm.

1649
01:46:04,500 --> 01:46:05,581
How you doing?

1650
01:46:05,660 --> 01:46:07,742
Oh, you know,
fair to middling.

1651
01:46:08,660 --> 01:46:10,071
Warming up?

1652
01:46:11,060 --> 01:46:12,710
I'm not sure yet.

1653
01:46:13,420 --> 01:46:15,900
Look like you are,
a little bit.

1654
01:46:17,900 --> 01:46:19,743
How's Rob doing?

1655
01:46:22,700 --> 01:46:24,987
Rob's still up
there right now.

1656
01:46:27,540 --> 01:46:29,588
And Doug?
What's he up to?

1657
01:46:34,700 --> 01:46:36,589
Doug's gone, Beck.

1658
01:46:52,540 --> 01:46:53,701
I don't know,
no one's ever tried

1659
01:46:53,780 --> 01:46:55,225
to fly higher than
Base Camp before,

1660
01:46:55,300 --> 01:46:57,109
they're gonna give it a go.

1661
01:46:57,180 --> 01:46:59,751
You find an LZ,
just mark it out with whatever you can.

1662
01:46:59,820 --> 01:47:02,300
Okay, worth a try.
Thanks, Guy.

1663
01:47:02,380 --> 01:47:03,825
Yeah?
Grab a Gatorade.

1664
01:47:03,900 --> 01:47:06,187
Got a chopper coming in,
we need to make an LZ.

1665
01:47:06,260 --> 01:47:08,422
We got a chopper
coming in!

1666
01:47:09,780 --> 01:47:11,623
Clear everyone
back to the tents!

1667
01:47:12,420 --> 01:47:13,420
Thanks.

1668
01:47:13,460 --> 01:47:15,269
Keep it clear,
keep this whole area clear.

1669
01:47:15,380 --> 01:47:16,381
Back away.

1670
01:47:16,460 --> 01:47:18,428
Come on,
come on.

1671
01:47:23,180 --> 01:47:24,700
<i>Army 45, keep updating.</i>

1672
01:47:25,300 --> 01:47:27,507
<i>Lukla Tower,
we're doing fine.</i>

1673
01:47:33,100 --> 01:47:35,182
It's not possible!

1674
01:47:35,460 --> 01:47:37,508
You land here,
we'll never get back up.

1675
01:47:42,820 --> 01:47:44,265
Gonna kill us!

1676
01:47:44,340 --> 01:47:46,149
Okay, Major, let's go back.

1677
01:48:04,940 --> 01:48:05,940
That's it!

1678
01:48:05,980 --> 01:48:08,586
We can't get any more out.
It's as light as we're gonna get it!

1679
01:48:08,660 --> 01:48:10,389
Time to
go then, Major.

1680
01:48:24,380 --> 01:48:26,348
Right here,
right here!

1681
01:48:28,700 --> 01:48:30,589
Come on!
You can do it!

1682
01:48:59,620 --> 01:49:02,226
Come on, buddy.
You're nearly there.

1683
01:49:05,580 --> 01:49:07,150
Okay, come on.

1684
01:49:10,140 --> 01:49:11,790
One person.
Only one person.

1685
01:49:11,860 --> 01:49:14,704
Yeah, it's just him, just one!
There.

1686
01:49:14,780 --> 01:49:16,225
There you go.

1687
01:49:19,460 --> 01:49:20,871
You're good!

1688
01:49:21,460 --> 01:49:24,669
I'm going to lift the tail up,
to fly us over the edge.

1689
01:49:24,740 --> 01:49:26,947
Fall a bit, until
the blades catch on the air.

1690
01:49:27,020 --> 01:49:28,226
Is that okay with you?

1691
01:49:28,300 --> 01:49:30,302
- I'm with you.
- Good man.

1692
01:50:49,820 --> 01:50:52,790
Get yourself inside,
go on.

1693
01:50:55,940 --> 01:50:57,180
Oh, Anatoli.

1694
01:51:03,540 --> 01:51:06,384
I'm so sorry, Helen.

1695
01:51:06,460 --> 01:51:08,667
Come on, let's
get you inside.

1696
01:51:30,540 --> 01:51:31,871
Hi, Peachy.

1697
01:51:36,860 --> 01:51:38,066
Hey.

1698
01:51:51,020 --> 01:51:53,546
Thank you
so much, darling.

